"{\"uid\": \"newseu.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-07-Olympics-scaling-up-climbing-opportunities-for-young-Parisians--1vPphoctIwU-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Ross Cullen in Paris  Copied  The Paris 2024 organizers aim to make young people the prime beneficiaries of the Olympic and Paralympic Games.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cThat's one of the key legacy aims, along with improving accessibility to open-water swimming in the River Seine, and turning the areas around Olympic venues into new neighborhoods.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cThe Climb-Up gym in southern Paris is the biggest indoor climbing center in France \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093\\u00a0but it's an outlier. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cThe capital region has a shortage of high-quality climbing facilities, according to the Games organizers.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cHowever, one thing it does not lack is willing participants. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cThere are three million children under five in France, and staff at the climbing center say that is the perfect age to try out sport climbing.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008c\\\"It's more practical to learn climbing when you are young, you are lighter, and more mobile,\\\" says Cathy Bremaud, the communications director at Climb-Up, who notes that children \\\"are much more comfortable with heights than adults. They always find a solution, and to climb the wall, and get up high despite the fact that they are smaller than us and they could be more scared because they have seen fewer things in life.\\\"  READ MORE  Palestinian Olympians pursue peace in Paris  The Olympics' fastest sport  Olympics boxing achieves gender equality  The sport of climbing is relatively new to the Olympics - debuting at Tokyo 2020. There, not to everyone's taste, a single event combined three disciplines: lead climbing, speed climbing and bouldering.  This time, speed climbing has been made a separate event, in which competitors scramble side-by-side up a 15-meter wall. Lead climbing and bouldering are still combined, in an event based on point-scoring rather than speed.  Bouldering takes place on walls no more than 4.5 meters high, without a rope. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cThe only special equipment you need is a pair of climbing shoes \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 and now that it's an Olympic sport, the climbing community has a defined route to success.  The staff at Climb-Up have witnessed a significant increase in the number of younger members since it opened in 2021.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008c\\\"When you are very young, your first reflex is grabbing or grasping,\\\" says Simon Brusco, the climbing development manager at Climb-Up.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008c\\\"Here that works well because people in Paris are always looking for something different, and so for the young ones a place like this works very well, and we put in place fun activities for them.\\\"  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cIt's one of the charms of the Olympic Games that it puts lesser-known sports in the spotlight. Climbing is one of those, and the Games organizers \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 determined to unlock the youth potential for the future \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 are handing over the Olympic climbing center to the local area once the Games are over.  Subscribe toStoryboard: A weekly newsletterbringing you the best of CGTN every Friday  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"